headlines.description: — Brandon Miller scored off an offensive rebound at the buzzer to lift Charlotte Hornets to a thrilling 108-107 victory over the Detroit Pistons on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brandon Miller's putback at the buzzer lifts Hornets to dramatic 108-107 victory

headlines.description: — Bennedict Mathurin scored 20 points, four teammates each had 17, and the Indiana Pacers defeated the Orlando Magic 118-111 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mathurin's 20 leads balanced Pacers past Magic, 118-111

events.name: New York Knicks at Atlanta Hawks

headlines.description: — No. 1 overall pick Zaccharie Risacher scored 33 points and had seven rebounds and the Atlanta Hawks rallied late to beat the New York Knicks 121-116 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 1 pick Zaccharie Risacher scores 33 as Hawks rally late to down Knicks 121-116

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Boston Celtics

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry scored 27 points, Buddy Hield had 16 and the Golden State Warriors beat the Boston Celtics 118-112 on Wednesday night for their fifth straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stephen Curry scores 27 points to lead Warriors past Celtics 118-112

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Houston Rockets

headlines.description: — Jalen Green and Fred VanVleet had 21 points each and the Houston Rockets built a huge lead early and coasted to a 127-100 win over the San Antonio Spurs Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Green and VanVleet score 21 each as Houston Rockets rout San Antonio Spurs 127-100

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Memphis Grizzlies

headlines.description: — Ja Morant scored 20 points before leaving in the third quarter with a right hamstring injury and the Memphis Grizzlies used their 3-point shooting to beat the Los Angeles Lakers 131-114 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Morant, Wells, Jackson Jr. score 20 apiece as Grizzlies beat Lakers 131-114

events.name: Cleveland Cavaliers at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell scored 29 points and the Cleveland Cavaliers defeated the New Orleans Pelicans 131-122 on Wednesday night to open 9-0 for the first time in their 55-year NBA history.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mitchell scores 29 and the Cavaliers beat the Pelicans 131-122 for their first 9-0 start

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic had 27 points and 13 assists, Kyrie Irving scored 17 points and Daniel Gafford also scored 17 playing a season-high 24 minutes as the Dallas Mavericks beat the Chicago Bulls 119-99 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Luka Doncic's 27 points, 13 assists lead Dallas Mavericks past Chicago Bulls 119-99

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Denver Nuggets

headlines.description: — Russell Westbrook scored 29 points, Peyton Watson blocked a shot in the closing seconds after missing a pair of free throws at the other end and the injury-riddled Denver Nuggets...
headlines.shortLinkText: Watson seals 124-122 win for Nuggets with blocked shot in final second, handing Thunder 1st loss

headlines.description: — Kevin Durant scored 32 points, Jusuf Nurkic had 20 points and 18 rebounds, and the Phoenix Suns rallied from a 15-point deficit Wednesday night to defeat the Miami Heat 115-112 and extend their winning streak to six games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Durant scores 32 points and Suns rally from 15 down to beat Heat 115-112 for 6th in a row

headlines.shortLinkText: Clippers beat the one-win 76ers 110-98 in Paul George's return to Los Angeles

headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan scored 27 points in a record-setting performance and the Sacramento Kings beat the Toronto Raptors 122-107 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: DeMar DeRozan scores 27 points to lead the Kings past the Raptors 122-107
